I had 57 GVoc Earth at this time and that worked pretty nice.<br>
<br>
I personally havent found the Bank area being worth it solo. They are reasonably harder and sometimes petty risky. <br>
I used to just run between WL and EW zones and killing everything that was green/lightblue.<br>
Now sometimes some random groups formed. And everyone is ok there because you arent for exp or something (at least I wasnt ;-) ) so any additional damage counts.<br>
When a Tank joined me sometimes I just told him that he has to care for himself to stay alive because I cant heal him, I offered to summon him arrows then so he can do &quot;safe&quot; range dmg.<br>
<br>
Sometimes I found enough people to really do bank area or even go to Arena.<br>
And once we got lucky and some guild pulled all Mobs between Bank area and Tormax/AoW(?) to bank area. So we just stood there and made sure we got the faction hits ;-)<br>
<br>
So...you can do the faction solo pretty nicely in there, but if you can ind some random people with the same aim: even better ;-) <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.euphorion.org/sig/euph_new2.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=marloon>Marloon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 40<br> <font color=#333333>(12/18/02 4:11:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1120.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   What about GD</span><hr size=1>   Ok, what about roaming giants in GD and the wolves?  They are all way too easy to kill and theres a lot of them around.  I mean, no matter what you not going to go from scowling to ally in a day, but yu can collect some pieces for your shawl quest by killing wolves and they are very very easy.  No epic, with a 10k burnt wood staff and a 130k horse needed for them either.  If you have a 8k horse it's kinda nice cause you can stay FM and nuke too.<br>
